 Solution: To solve this problem we must know the following relationships:
\[
\begin{aligned}
v \lambda &=c\\
\frac{1}{\lambda} &= \frac{v}{c}
\end{aligned}
\]

Given that $v = 7.353e14 s^{-1}$ and $c = 3 \times 10^{8} m / s$, we can calculate the wave number as follows:
\[
\begin{aligned}
\frac{1}{\lambda} &= \frac{v}{c}\\
&= \frac{7.353e14 s^{-1}}{3 \times 10^{8} m / s}\\
&= 2.451e6 m^{-1}
\end{aligned}
\]

Final answer: The final answer is 2.451e6. I hope it is correct.
